{"parentUuid":"bb8946d3-35f2-4983-8910-5b9952bea833","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"fe6dfd78-a024-427f-8603-e462c99e8561","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PyGRWmpauFAMXSPwxa84un","type":"tool_result","content":"   542→        for slot in slots:\n   543→            code_slot = int(slot[\"code_slot\"])\n   544→            usercode: str = slot[\"usercode\"] or \"\"\n   545→            in_use: bool | None = slot[\"in_use\"]\n   546→\n   547→            if not in_use:\n   548→                data[code_slot] = SlotCode.EMPTY\n   549→            elif not usercode:\n   550→                # in_use but no code content (cache partially populated); skip\n   551→                continue\n   552→            elif usercode == \"*\" * len(usercode):\n   553→                # Masked code (all asterisks with slot in use)\n   554→                data[code_slot] = SlotCode.UNKNOWN\n   555→            else:\n   556→                # Unmasked code\n   557→                data[code_slot] = usercode\n   558→\n   559→        slots_with_pin = [s for s, v in data.items() if v is not SlotCode.EMPTY]\n   560→        slots_empty = [s for s, v in data.items() if v is SlotCode.EMPTY]\n   561→        _LOGGER.debug(\n   562→            \"Lock %s: %s slots with PIN %s, %s slots empty %s\",\n   563→            self.lock.entity_id,\n   564→            len(slots_with_pin),\n   565→            slots_with_pin,\n   566→            len(slots_empty),\n   567→            slots_empty,\n   568→        )\n   569→        return data\n   570→"}]},"uuid":"e2b1a403-f931-4b96-8fd1-f2f769c0d07f","timestamp":"2026-04-04T22:42:54.863Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager/custom_components/lock_code_manager/providers/zwave_js.py","content":"        for slot in slots:\n            code_slot = int(slot[\"code_slot\"])\n            usercode: str = slot[\"usercode\"] or \"\"\n            in_use: bool | None = slot[\"in_use\"]\n\n            if not in_use:\n                data[code_slot] = SlotCode.EMPTY\n            elif not usercode:\n                # in_use but no code content (cache partially populated); skip\n                continue\n            elif usercode == \"*\" * len(usercode):\n                # Masked code (all asterisks with slot in use)\n                data[code_slot] = SlotCode.UNKNOWN\n            else:\n                # Unmasked code\n                data[code_slot] = usercode\n\n        slots_with_pin = [s for s, v in data.items() if v is not SlotCode.EMPTY]\n        slots_empty = [s for s, v in data.items() if v is SlotCode.EMPTY]\n        _LOGGER.debug(\n            \"Lock %s: %s slots with PIN %s, %s slots empty %s\",\n            self.lock.entity_id,\n            len(slots_with_pin),\n            slots_with_pin,\n            len(slots_empty),\n            slots_empty,\n        )\n        return data\n","numLines":29,"startLine":542,"totalLines":570}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"bb8946d3-35f2-4983-8910-5b9952bea833","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"e2b1a403-f931-4b96-8fd1-f2f769c0d07f","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01FLw6Pet25sp7TW48x53bin","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You're right — Z-Wave already returns *all* slots from the cache (line 542 iterates all `slots`, not just `code_slots`). The `code_slots` set is computed but only used for the hard refresh check (lines 530-540), not for filtering the output. So Z-Wave's `async_get_usercodes` already returns unmanaged slots.\n\nMatter and Virtual artificially filter. So option B is actually just making Matter/Virtual consistent with Z-Wave — return all occupied slots, let callers filter. The coordinator already handles extra slots fine (it just stores whatever the provider returns).\n\nLet me fix Matter and Virtual to return all occupied slots."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":523,"cache_read_input_tokens":346302,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":523},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZjYDJBGKHSkPfJW7DAwQ","type":"assistant","uuid":"a418d6ec-4fe4-4bdd-a2dd-fad843fd5ede","timestamp":"2026-04-04T22:43:03.097Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
